      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite and change-log traceability to regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Solver is version-controlled and a unit-test suite exists, but formal qualification documentation and change-log traceability required for MRL 5 Class III submission are incomplete. Achieved level 2 falls short of the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations with demonstrated convergence rates matching theoretical order.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was applied to the Navier-Stokes solver but not to the hemolysis transport sub-model. Convergence order confirmed for flow equations only; hemolysis scalar transport lacks independent verification. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for hemolysis QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes with GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation completed; GCI for pressure-head is 3.1%, but GCI for the hemolysis index QoI is 11.4%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Spatial discretization error in the hemolysis scalar field is not adequately controlled at MRL 5. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions match COU operating envelope within documented tolerances; blood analogue rheology characterised.",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments used porcine blood at a single haematocrit. COU requires human blood across a haematocrit range of 30–45%. Rheological mismatch between test and COU conditions is unquantified. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty) computed for hemolysis index across all 5 operating points with statistical confidence bounds.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions compared at 3 of 5 required operating points. Validation metric computed without accounting for experimental measurement uncertainty. Two operating points outside validated range. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI is the normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) directly used in clinical acceptance criterion; secondary QoIs include shear stress distribution.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and is directly mapped to the clinical threshold. Shear stress distributions are reported but not formally linked to the acceptance criterion. Minor gap in QoI traceability. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under VAD operating conditions; results extrapolation to clinical device justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic pump, which differs geometrically from the clinical VAD device. Extrapolation to clinical geometry is asserted but not supported by a formal similarity analysis. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria tightened until QoI changes by less than 0.1% between successive iterations; round-off error estimated.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence not formally assessed for the hemolysis transport equation. Residual drop criterion used for flow equations was not re-evaluated after coupling to the hemolysis sub-model. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing by a qualified analyst not involved in original analysis.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup or post-processing has been conducted. Use error assessment is absent. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Alternative turbulence and hemolysis constitutive models evaluated; model-form uncertainty bounded through ensemble of plausible model choices.",
      "rationale": "A single turbulence model (SST k-omega) and a single hemolysis constitutive law (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) were used. No alternative model forms evaluated. Model-form uncertainty is uncharacterised. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and boundary condition inputs characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation completed; dominant input drivers identified via sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed propagating uncertainty in blood viscosity, inlet flow rate, and rotational speed through the CFD model. Output statistics (mean NIH, 95th percentile) are reported. However, no sensitivity analysis has been conducted to identify which input parameters drive output variance — the dominant contributors to hemolysis prediction uncertainty remain uncharacterised. The team noted that 'we plan to extend with sensitivity analysis in a subsequent revision' but this work has not been completed and no sensitivity analysis artifact is linked to this package. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Statistical characterisation of experimental sample variability (n >= 5 replicates per operating point) with confidence intervals propagated into validation metric.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were performed with n=2 replicates per operating point. Sample variability is not statistically characterised and confidence intervals are not propagated into the validation metric. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping between experimental boundary conditions and simulation inputs documented; any discrepancies quantified and their effect on QoI bounded.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions used in simulation were set from nominal pump operating specifications rather than measured experimental conditions. Equivalency between experimental and simulation inputs has not been formally assessed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-not-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated against MRL 5 requirements. Seven factors were formally assessed; in each case the achieved level falls below the required level. Six factors were flagged as not-assessed, representing epistemic gaps that cannot be resolved without additional experimental and analytical work. Monte Carlo UQ has been completed and output statistics are available. Notably, the dominant input drivers of hemolysis prediction uncertainty have not been identified because no sensitivity analysis has been linked to this package; the team's stated intention to perform sensitivity analysis in a future revision does not satisfy the current MRL 5 credibility requirement for model inputs. The overall credibility package does not meet the requirements for a Class III VAD submission at MRL 5. Decision: Not accepted pending resolution of all identified gaps.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
